equals

public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
Compares the specified object with this object for equality. Returns true if and only if the specified object is also a PersistentObject and this.getId().compareTo(persistentObject2.getId()) == 0. In other words, two persistentObjects are defined to be equal if they have the same id.
